reviewText:
First of all I must say that I'm not easily impressed by the modern video games, but after finishing this game, the wow effect, that has been reached by the intergalactic flying sofa (the sofa was the last drop), made me want to share and recommend this game to my friends.

The game kicks off slowly, without giving a hint of the story. I could not tell how the story would end, whereas in the majority of the modern video games it is easy to predict how exactly the plot is going to unfold since the very beginning. Since I'm a man who believes in traditional values, without spoiling the plot, I must say that I was touched by the ending.

This game is a great mixture of several genres, it can be described as an adventure platformer with the elements of puzzle. This is exactly the type of game I was looking for. It kept me entertained from the beginning till the very end and I enjoyed every piece of it:
Funny, blabberish NPC voice acting;
Gravel tossing while climbing the sky staircase on your journey from the farmland (loved the soundtrack by the way) to the outer space;
Chaotic rockets on the moon that occasionally blow you up;
Mission impossible themed castle and much more...

Tl:dr - I recommend this game to those who are fond of challenging and atmospheric adventure platformers. (10/10 - soundtrack, story, atmosphere, challenge).
However, I do not recommend this game to the everbored people (the ones who are usually saying that they are forced" to collect achievements

